Backend 
The backend is developed using Flask. Routing is used to connect URLs to specific functions. Each route handles a particular feature such as login, adding tasks, or uploading files. SQLite is used as the database, which is lightweight and does not require server setup. SQL queries are used to insert, update, retrieve, and delete data.

Frontend
The frontend is built using HTML and CSS. Jinja templating is used to dynamically display data from the backend. Templates extend a base layout to maintain consistency across pages.
CSS is used to create a modern dark-themed interface with responsive design and styled components such as buttons, forms, and cards.

